      {
        "name": "overview",
        "title": "Overview",
        "elements": [
          {
            "type": "html",
            "name": "overview_html",
            "html": "<p><strong>Quintana et al. (2026)</strong> — <em>It is not always greener on the other side: Greenery perception across demographics and personalities in multiple cities</em>. <em>Landscape and Urban Planning</em>, 271, 105618. <a href=\"https://doi.org/10.1016/j.landurbplan.2026.105618\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\">https://doi.org/10.1016/j.landurbplan.2026.105618</a></p><p>This template reproduces the <strong>greenery-focused</strong> branch of the SPECS survey: demographics + Big Five personality, then pairwise ratings for <strong>“Which place looks greener?”</strong> (5 pairs; left / right / equal).</p><p>Related dataset &amp; code: <a href=\"https://github.com/matqr/specs\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\">SPECS</a>, <a href=\"https://github.com/matqr/greenery-perception\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\">greenery-perception</a>, <a href=\"https://huggingface.co/datasets/matiasqr/specs\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\">HF: matiasqr/specs</a>, <a href=\"https://huggingface.co/datasets/matiasqr/greenery-perception\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\">HF: matiasqr/greenery-perception</a>.</p><p>Full multi-indicator SPECS instrument is also available as template <code>2025-quintana-specs</code>.</p>"
          }
        ]
